race.comment: DEFENSEMEN (2) beautifully bred Wootton Bassett colt from American mare Upfront making his debut for the Waller yard. Looked a real professional when a dominant trial winner over 900m at Rosehill. Ticks plenty of boxes from an inside gate. PEARL OF DUBAI (7) Wootton Bassett filly from the well related mare Al Anood on debut for the Peter Snowden yard. Her second trial looked much better when a sharp winner over 805m at Warwick Farm. From a top juvenile stable and worth noting Berry rode her in both trials. PREDATION (6) Capitalist colt from the good race mare Ygritte on debut for the Edward O'Rourke stable. Slow into stride before rounding them up effortlessly when a 900m trial winner at Rosehill. Genuine contender who will be strong late. LORD ELROND (5) is a Shalaa colt from Queen Of Wands having his first start for the O'Shea & Charlton stable. Given the two trials and looks set for a bold debut. KING CAMPANIA (4) is on debut for the Waller yard and had no luck in his only trial.
